*** RootServ Operator Help - Command: REGIONS ***
Manipulates the Regions list.
 
Syntax: REGIONS ADDCIDR mask region reason
        REGIONS ADDHOST mask region reason
        REGIONS DELCIDR mask
        REGIONS DELHOST mask
        REGIONS CHREASON mask new-reason
        REGIONS RLIST
        REGIONS LIST [region] [start [end]] [pattern]
 
ADDCIDR adds a CIDR-type host (i.e. 127.0.0.0/8) to the region specified.
 
DELCIDR removes a CIDR-type host from the region specified, if present.
 
ADDHOST adds a host (i.e. *.azzurra.chat) to the region specified.
 
DELHOST removes a host from the region specified, if present.
 
CHREASON changes the reason for a host/CIDR.
 
RLIST returns a list of currently available regions.
 
LIST returns a list of CIDRs/hosts for the specified region.
 
*** End of OHelp ***